---
// Isolated harness for the connection panel — issue #151 t13.
//
// The real page is src/pages/index.astro, which reserves
// `#connection-mount` for this component; but three wave-2 tasks build
// inside site/ in parallel and all three would collide editing that one
// file, so index.astro is wired by the coordinator after they merge. This
// page exists so the panel can be run, seen and driven on its own in the
// meantime — and it stays useful afterwards: it is the smallest page that
// reproduces a proxy or credential problem with nothing else on it.
//
// It is not linked from the site nav. Open it directly at /dev-connection.
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import ConnectionPanel from "../components/ConnectionPanel.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Connection — lobes realtime test harness"
  description="Isolated harness for the /v1/realtime connection controls: open and close a session through the local credential-injecting proxy."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">t13 · dev harness</span>
      <h1>Connection</h1>
      <p class="lede muted">
        One <code>/v1/realtime</code> session, opened and closed by hand,
        through the local proxy that holds the credential. This page carries
        nothing else — no mic, no event log — so a failure here is a failure
        of the connection path and nothing more.
      </p>

      <div class="card panel-host">
        <ConnectionPanel />
      </div>

      <div class="prose notes">
        <h2>If it will not connect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Is this page served by <code>npm run dev</code>?</strong> The
            proxy lives in the dev server. A built site served any other way has
            no route to the gateway at all — by design.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Is the gateway reachable at <code>LOBES_GATEWAY_URL</code>?</strong>
            Off-box, that means an <code>ssh -L</code> forward is up — see the
            README.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Does the credential match?</strong> Press <em>Check gateway</em>.
            A failed WebSocket handshake looks identical for every cause; the
            check sees the HTTP status the socket cannot.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .panel-host {
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }

  .notes {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .notes ul {
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .notes li {
    line-height: 1.65;
  }
</style>
